{"word":"ἐπινοέω","slug":"ἐπινοέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐπινοέω</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>ήσω</el>) </el><p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to think on</i> or <i>of, contrive</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, attic: —<a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>:—<a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a> <i>to form plans, to plan, invent</i>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>to have in one's mind, intend, purpose</i>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>: <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>aor1 <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>pass.</a></a> <el>ἐπινοήθην</el> is used like <a href='S:active signification'><a href='S:Active voice'>Act.</a></a>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}